WEBVTT

00:04.134 --> 00:07.433
<i>[ Chorus ]
# The Simpsons #</i>

00:08.514 --> 00:10.814
 DAYS OF WINE AND D'OH'SES

00:18.215 --> 00:20.115
<i>[ Bell Ringing ]</i>

00:24.989 --> 00:27.958
<i>[ Whistle Blowing ]</i>

00:30.527 --> 00:32.427
[ Beeping ]

00:38.068 --> 00:39.968
## [Jazzy Solo ]

00:41.000 --> 00:47.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:00.057 --> 01:01.957
[ Beeping ]

01:02.059 --> 01:04.027
[ Tires Screeching ]

01:05.361 --> 01:07.262
D'oh!
[ Screams ]

01:11.001 --> 01:12.969
[ All Screaming ]

01:25.482 --> 01:30.283
<i>Ah, trash night. In France they call it
''la nuit de poubelle. ''</i>

01:30.387 --> 01:32.981
<i>In Germany it's ''crappenfest.''</i>

01:33.090 --> 01:36.059
I can't believe it only
comes 52 times a year.

01:36.160 --> 01:38.424
Quit gabbin' and start grabbin'.

01:38.529 --> 01:41.191
And remember, the best stuff is usually
deep in the garbage juice.

01:41.298 --> 01:45.166
<i>[ Grunting ]
See? A new pacifier for Maggie.</i>

01:46.303 --> 01:49.568
Lookee here!
Cardy-board tubes!

01:49.673 --> 01:53.837
Now we can have indoor plumbin',
just like they's got at the women's lockup.

01:53.944 --> 01:55.935
They spoilt you, Brandine.

01:56.046 --> 01:59.641
Sometimes I don't even know
who you are anymore.

02:01.185 --> 02:04.279
Ha! Look like Milhouse's mom
finally threw out his blankie.

02:04.388 --> 02:06.356
He'll pay a lot to get this back.

02:06.457 --> 02:09.017
Especially when we send it
to him piece by piece.

02:09.126 --> 02:11.390
<i>- [ Both Laughing ]
- [ Groaning ]</i>

02:11.495 --> 02:13.690
## [ Humming ]

02:13.797 --> 02:15.697
Shh! Quiet.

02:15.799 --> 02:20.202
<i>It seems I will never sell these
She-Hulk vs. Leon Spinks comics.</i>

02:20.304 --> 02:22.772
Worst crossover ever.

02:24.475 --> 02:26.670
- [ Sniffing ]
- Yeah.

02:26.777 --> 02:29.644
<i>[ Sniffing, Grunting ]</i>

02:30.881 --> 02:33.315
- [ Screaming ]
- Shoo, nerds! Shoo!

02:33.417 --> 02:34.611
[ Muttering ]

02:37.121 --> 02:39.351
Well, this muscle shirt's
a pretty good find.

02:39.456 --> 02:41.356
Dad, that's a sports bra.

02:41.458 --> 02:44.325
All I know is I'm finally
getting the support I need.

02:44.428 --> 02:46.453
Look, Dad!
Barber hair!

02:46.563 --> 02:48.895
[ Sniffing ]
Ooh, Italian.

02:50.100 --> 02:53.228
[ Chuckles ]
Hey, Vinnie. How's about a pizza?

02:53.337 --> 02:55.498
I got-a no job.
[ Chuckles ]

02:55.606 --> 02:59.440
<i>[ Gasps ] Mamma mia!
Look what the Hawaiian restaurant threw out.</i>

02:59.543 --> 03:02.512
<i>Get out of my dreams
and into my car.</i>

03:02.613 --> 03:04.638
<i>[ High-pitched Humming ]</i>

03:04.748 --> 03:09.117
<i>- [ Humming Continues ]
- I don't remember the air in the kitchen
being so wavy.</i>

03:09.219 --> 03:12.188
<i>[ Sniffs ]
Good lord! That's gas!</i>

03:12.289 --> 03:15.349
<i>[ Groans ]
Hmm.</i>

03:15.459 --> 03:17.825
- Hmm?
- [ Homer's Voice ] Behold!

03:17.928 --> 03:19.953
I am King Talkie Tiki!

03:20.064 --> 03:21.964
[ Screaming ]

03:22.066 --> 03:24.660
Hey, Flanders.
Can your god do that?

03:24.768 --> 03:28.169
A-Actually, Homer, you and I
worship the same god, so-

03:28.272 --> 03:32.009
Irregardless!
I am your god now.

03:33.914 --> 03:36.314
Homer you can just re-wrap the gas line

03:36.715 --> 03:40.708
- Do you know how dangerous that is?
- Do not anger Talkie Tiki!

03:40.818 --> 03:42.877
I am all power-

03:42.986 --> 03:45.511
[ Screams ] I'll be at Moe's.
[ Whimpering ]

03:47.091 --> 03:48.991
So I says to the cop, ''No...

03:49.093 --> 03:52.460
<i>you're driving under the influence
of bein' a jerk!''</i>

03:52.563 --> 03:55.327
[ Laughing ]

03:55.432 --> 03:58.765
- [ Sighs ]
- Hey, Barney, what's with the glum face?

03:58.869 --> 04:01.133
You glum or somethin'?
Huh, glummy?

04:01.238 --> 04:05.368
You know, it was my birthday last week
and no one remembered.

04:05.476 --> 04:08.343
- What are you, nuts?
- I threw you a party at my house.

04:08.445 --> 04:11.812
You lie! Why would I
not remember my own-

04:11.915 --> 04:14.713
<i>[ Gulps, Sighs ]
birthday?</i>

04:14.818 --> 04:19.118
But we did have a shindig for you, Barn.
We even videotaped it. Look.

04:23.193 --> 04:26.185
[ Moe ]
Oh, that's it, baby. All for Moe.

04:26.296 --> 04:29.629
Oh, yeah, work the slot.
Show me the package.

04:29.733 --> 04:32.827
Whoa. [ Laughs ]
That's-That's a project I'm workin' on. Sorry.

04:34.238 --> 04:36.138
[ Bart ]
Okay, Mom. We're rollin'.

04:36.240 --> 04:39.573
I wrote a poem for Barney
on this special occasion.

04:39.676 --> 04:43.442
''Now that you're one year older,
the time flew by so fast''-

04:43.547 --> 04:45.014
- Bart.
- [ Bart Laughing ]

04:45.115 --> 04:47.015
<i>Give me that.
[ Groans ]</i>

04:47.117 --> 04:50.450
I'm just sayin' that when we die...

04:50.554 --> 04:54.581
there's gonna be a planet for the French,
a planet for the Chinese...

04:54.691 --> 04:56.750
and we'll all be a lot happier.

04:56.860 --> 04:59.590
<i>- Mr. Gumble, you're upsetting me.
- No, I'm not.</i>

04:59.696 --> 05:03.723
<i>Gee. Is that what
I look like when I'm drunk?</i>

05:03.834 --> 05:08.032
You wish. That's the stage
we call ''Professor Barney.''

05:08.138 --> 05:12.370
<i>Talkative, coherent, even insightful.
Here's drunk.</i>

05:12.476 --> 05:14.376
[ Stairs Squeaking ]

05:14.478 --> 05:18.915
[ High-pitched Voice ]
Well, I'm off to market. [ Burps ]

05:19.016 --> 05:21.507
Marge, you're making
a complete fool of yours-

05:21.618 --> 05:23.518
Oh, it's just Barney.

05:23.620 --> 05:26.316
[ Shouts ]

05:26.423 --> 05:30.723
<i>[ Gasps ]
Precious alcohol, soaking in the shag!</i>

05:30.827 --> 05:33.261
<i>[ Gulping ]</i>

05:33.363 --> 05:36.093
<i>- [ Growling ]
- [ Whining ]</i>

05:36.200 --> 05:39.135
Oh. How embarrassing.

05:39.236 --> 05:42.399
- Well, how did this happen?
- Oh, that. You've had that for a while.

05:42.506 --> 05:45.771
Yeah, I can't really
picture you without it.

05:45.876 --> 05:48.037
Oh, I'm a disgrace!

05:48.145 --> 05:50.238
Disgracefully hilarious.

05:50.347 --> 05:53.339
You passed out before we could
even give you your presents.

05:53.450 --> 05:56.681
I still got mine. Barney, I got you
what no drunk can do without-

05:56.787 --> 05:59.255
<i>morning-after stationery.</i>

05:59.356 --> 06:03.258
- [ Laughing ]
- And I got you helicopter-flyin' lessons.

06:03.360 --> 06:06.454
Can you imagine this booze-bag
at the wheel of a whirlybird?

06:06.563 --> 06:08.656
[ Laughs ]
He'd be all, ''Look at me!

06:08.765 --> 06:11.063
I'm a tanked-up loser
in a helicopter!''

06:11.168 --> 06:13.636
[ Laughing ]

06:13.737 --> 06:17.173
Ah, anyway, happy b-day, pumpkin.

06:18.242 --> 06:21.405
So, I'm a tanked-up loser?

06:21.511 --> 06:23.445
Is that how you see me?

06:23.547 --> 06:28.041
Oh, sounds like a certain loser
could use some tankin' up.

06:29.453 --> 06:31.717
<i>- [ Grunts ]
- Hey, hey. Where you goin'?</i>

06:31.822 --> 06:35.383
I'll show you.
I'm gonna take these helicopter lessons.

06:35.492 --> 06:39.952
Wait a minute, Barney. You gotta be sober to fly.
I mean, it's not like driving a car.

06:40.063 --> 06:43.794
- Then I'm gonna quit drinkin'!
- [ Laughing ]

06:43.900 --> 06:46.425
- No, I mean it.
- [ Laughing Continues ]

06:46.536 --> 06:49.471
You won't see me here again, ever!

06:53.744 --> 06:55.678
Wait. That ain't funny.
He's my best customer.

06:55.779 --> 06:58.043
Well, the handwriting's on the wall.

06:58.148 --> 07:00.742
To stay afloat, this bar
is gonna have to go queer.

07:00.851 --> 07:02.842
You mean it's not? Oh.
[ Clicks Tongue ]

07:02.953 --> 07:05.649
<i>Wrong again,
Gay Guide to Springfield.</i>

07:11.194 --> 07:13.788
Farewell, my longneck friends.

07:13.897 --> 07:15.489
<i>[ Grunts ]</i>

07:18.135 --> 07:20.103
[ Shatters ]

07:21.338 --> 07:23.238
All right, world.

07:23.340 --> 07:26.901
<i>Get ready to meet
the clean and sober Barney Gumble.</i>

07:28.578 --> 07:31.240
<i>Whee! Give me a beer.</i>

07:31.348 --> 07:33.339
I knew you'd be back.

07:33.450 --> 07:35.543
Santeria, you're the greatest.

07:36.853 --> 07:39.253
Barney, didn't you say you
were going to stop drinking?

07:39.356 --> 07:43.884
I know, but it's so hard!
Please help me, Homer.

07:43.994 --> 07:48.363
You came to the right guy. I'll straighten you out...
right after I finish this beer.

07:48.465 --> 07:50.933
<i>- Mmm. [ Gulping ]
- Ohh.</i>

07:51.034 --> 07:53.901
- Mmm.
- Ohh.

07:54.004 --> 07:57.531
[ Mumbling ]
Oh, man, that's sweet.

07:57.641 --> 07:59.575
Okay, let's go.

07:59.676 --> 08:04.409
My name is Barney,
and I'm an alcoholic.

08:04.514 --> 08:07.972
I feel for you, pally, but, uh, you want A.A.
This is Triple ''A.''

08:08.085 --> 08:10.952
Oh. My name is Homer,
and I'm planning a trip to Saint Louis.

08:11.054 --> 08:14.080
- East Saint Louis?
- Is there any other Saint Louis?

08:15.625 --> 08:19.152
<i>[ Chattering ]</i>

08:20.197 --> 08:22.290
Uh, welcome back, Homer.

08:22.399 --> 08:24.993
I see you finally hit rock bottom.

08:25.102 --> 08:28.299
<i>[ Raspberries ]
Not a chance. I can sink way lower.</i>

08:28.405 --> 08:30.430
I just came to help
my friend Barney.

08:30.540 --> 08:32.565
We all know why
we're here, don't we?

08:32.676 --> 08:36.476
To keep ourselves sober, and to network.
So let's get started.

08:36.580 --> 08:39.309
Well, after I lost
my third job in two days...

08:39.416 --> 08:41.679
<i>old Gil was in a pit of despair.</i>

08:41.784 --> 08:44.310
And that's when you realized
you were an alcoholic?

08:44.421 --> 08:48.881
Oh, no, I never touch the stuff. But you don't
have to be drunk to know the value of Amway.

08:48.992 --> 08:51.893
<i>- [ Gasping ]
- Now, this is used crankcase oil...</i>

08:51.995 --> 08:54.520
<i>which you ladies know
is murder to clean up,you know?</i>

08:54.631 --> 08:56.531
And company's coming-

08:56.633 --> 09:01.002
Oh! You're doing this at the worst possible time.
Oh, your finger's in my eye!

09:02.839 --> 09:05.865
I have a problem with alcohol
and I need help.

09:05.976 --> 09:08.206
Well, your recovery begins today.

09:08.311 --> 09:12.179
And we promise you all the sugar cookies
and secondhand smoke you can handle.

09:12.282 --> 09:14.580
These sugar cookies you speak of...

09:14.684 --> 09:16.652
are they real or symbolic?

09:16.753 --> 09:19.221
They're on that table over there.

09:19.322 --> 09:21.347
Oh, I don't wanna walk that far.

09:21.458 --> 09:25.588
Anything that takes 1 2 steps
isn't worth doin'.

09:25.695 --> 09:28.892
<i>Get it? Huh? Twelve?
[ Laughs ]</i>

09:28.999 --> 09:31.058
<i>Steps?
[ Giggles ]</i>

09:31.168 --> 09:33.762
Hey, how did I get out here?

09:33.870 --> 09:38.034
<i>- ## [ Instrumental ]
- [ Giggles ] Hurt everyone.</i>

09:38.141 --> 09:41.668
<i>- Did Ga Ga just say ''Hurt everyone''?
- [ Laughs ] Ga Ga- Cute name.</i>

09:41.778 --> 09:46.374
- [ Man ] The Springfield
phone book needs a new cover.
- [ Together] It does?

09:46.483 --> 09:50.852
Send us your snapshots, and if we select yours,
you win a fabulous mystery prize.

09:50.954 --> 09:53.115
To enter, send your film
to this address.

09:53.223 --> 09:55.123
Too quick? Try again.

09:55.225 --> 09:57.125
Did you get it?
Here it is.

09:57.227 --> 09:59.957
Coming in from the left.
Don't delay. Do it today!

10:00.063 --> 10:03.726
- You think we should enter?
- Well, it shouldn't be too hard
to beat the old photo.

10:03.834 --> 10:04.926
<i>[ Bart ]
Ugh.</i>

10:07.304 --> 10:09.864
<i>- Hmm.
- It's gotta be here somewhere.</i>

10:09.973 --> 10:12.100
Hmm. Hmm. Hmm.

10:12.209 --> 10:14.370
Hey, here's a camera.

10:15.779 --> 10:18.043
And it's still got
a roll of film in it.

10:18.148 --> 10:21.606
Man, these old cameras
are really built solid.

10:21.718 --> 10:25.085
- Bart, we need that to win the contest.
- Win the what now?

10:26.923 --> 10:29.517
[ No Audible Dialogue ]

10:29.626 --> 10:32.925
[ Inhales, Exhales ]
Here goes.

10:33.029 --> 10:37.830
So he's so busy worrying about the front rotor,
he walks right into the back one.

10:38.935 --> 10:40.835
Only in this business.

10:40.937 --> 10:43.770
I'd like to sign up
for helicopter lessons.

10:43.874 --> 10:48.072
Sorry, pal, but it takes a special kind of man
to pilot these birds.

10:48.178 --> 10:50.112
- I got a coupon.
- Okay, get in.

10:53.183 --> 10:56.710
Elvis played a chopper pilot one time.
[ Chuckles ]

10:56.820 --> 10:59.380
He made so many darn mistakes...

10:59.489 --> 11:01.389
we were just laughin' at him.

11:01.491 --> 11:03.755
<i>- Great singer though.
- Oh, absolutely.</i>

11:03.860 --> 11:07.387
You know who else I like
is that, uh, Leo Sayer.

11:07.497 --> 11:09.556
Anyway, we're nice and level now.

11:09.666 --> 11:11.691
How would you like
to take the controls?

11:11.801 --> 11:14.497
- You think I'm ready?
- Sure, I do.

11:14.604 --> 11:17.368
One sec. Testing, black box.
One, two.

11:17.474 --> 11:20.204
[ Screaming ]

11:20.310 --> 11:22.210
She's all yours, friend.

11:22.312 --> 11:24.678
<i>[ Grunting ]</i>

11:24.781 --> 11:27.443
Whoa. Whoa. Whoa.

11:27.551 --> 11:30.315
Whoa. Hey, I think I'm gettin' it!

11:30.420 --> 11:32.320
Yes, that's great.

11:32.422 --> 11:35.755
Now let's just pull ourselves
out of this tailspin here.

11:35.859 --> 11:38.123
<i>[ Grunting ]</i>

11:38.228 --> 11:40.526
Whoo. Oh, I'm sorry about that.

11:40.630 --> 11:42.928
It's okay. That's what
the diapers are for.

11:46.002 --> 11:50.302
Now when the mama bird returns to feed
her babies we'll have a prize-winning picture.

11:50.407 --> 11:53.205
Lisa, people these days
don't wanna see a baby bird.

11:53.310 --> 11:55.369
They wanna see celebrities
at their worst.

11:55.478 --> 11:57.446
<i>[ Bell Dings ]</i>

11:58.615 --> 12:00.674
- Mmm. Mmm.
- Is that Rainier Wolfcastle?

12:00.784 --> 12:03.116
- Check out the gut.
- It's for a movie.

12:03.219 --> 12:06.655
I'm playing a fat secret agent.
Mmm. Mmm.

12:09.693 --> 12:12.161
Hey, Homer. Uh, no, no, no.
Don't sit there.

12:12.262 --> 12:14.162
Take this seat-
right next to the tap.

12:14.264 --> 12:16.494
But that's Barney's seat.

12:16.600 --> 12:18.625
Are you trying to make me
the new Barney?

12:18.735 --> 12:21.431
Hey, every bar needs
a world-class drunk.

12:21.538 --> 12:24.564
Yeah, someone who makes our alcoholism
seems less raging.

12:24.674 --> 12:27.973
Well, forget it, guys.
I am not Barney.

12:28.078 --> 12:31.104
- [ Burps ]
- [ Laughing ]

12:31.214 --> 12:33.614
See, Homer?
It's not so bad.

12:33.717 --> 12:36.049
- Now dance, rummy.
- O-Okay.

12:36.152 --> 12:41.954
## [ Humming ]

12:43.693 --> 12:46.958
You danced for hours just
because they told you to?

12:47.063 --> 12:49.088
If I didn't, I'd lose their respect.

12:49.199 --> 12:51.224
<i>- [ Helicopter Whirring ]
- Huh?</i>

12:51.334 --> 12:54.167
<i>- [ Gasps ]
- Check it out, Homer. I'm flyin' this thing.</i>

12:54.270 --> 12:56.204
<i>Get it away from the house!</i>

12:56.306 --> 12:58.706
- Wanna go for a ride?
- Can I, Marge? Can I?

12:58.808 --> 13:00.605
<i>- Yes, go.Just go.
- [ Yowls ]</i>

13:03.013 --> 13:05.538
Oh, you missed some
big changes at Moe's.

13:05.649 --> 13:08.209
He hangs newspapers
over the urinals now.

13:08.318 --> 13:10.843
You can read the sports page
while you pee.

13:10.954 --> 13:13.047
Very la-di-da.

13:13.156 --> 13:15.124
I've made some big changes too.

13:15.225 --> 13:17.193
Can you believe
I'm flyin' this helicopter?

13:17.293 --> 13:19.193
- Power lines. Power lines!
- Whoops. Sorry.

13:19.295 --> 13:21.126
Whoa!

13:21.231 --> 13:25.861
- When I think about all the time
I wasted at Moe's-
- Wasted?

13:25.969 --> 13:27.994
What about our staring contests?

13:28.104 --> 13:31.039
And the way we always knew
what football coaches should've done.

13:31.141 --> 13:34.338
Remember the day we jumped that census guy
and stole his clicker?

13:34.444 --> 13:36.935
Those are all
priceless memories, Homer...

13:37.047 --> 13:39.572
but I don't wanna do
that stuff anymore.

13:39.683 --> 13:44.120
- Oh, so you're better than me. Is that it?
- I didn't say that.

13:44.220 --> 13:46.347
- Take me home.
- Oh, don't be that way, Homer.

13:46.456 --> 13:48.447
- I'll scream.
- Okay, okay.

13:53.630 --> 13:55.530
So how was your ride with Barney?

13:55.632 --> 13:58.032
I don't wanna talk about it.
[ Sobbing ]

13:58.134 --> 14:00.398
<i>- [ Door Closes ]
- [ Sobbing Continues ]</i>

14:00.503 --> 14:02.403
[ Mumbles ]

14:07.243 --> 14:09.973
[ Mumbling ]

14:10.080 --> 14:13.481
<i>[ Grunting ]
Stupid Barney. Thinks he's too good for me.</i>

14:13.583 --> 14:17.075
Cheer up, Homie.
You don't need friends to be happy.

14:17.187 --> 14:19.417
I haven't had a friend in years.

14:19.522 --> 14:21.717
But you got me.
Who have I got?

14:21.825 --> 14:25.192
Oh. Well, you still
have Lenny and Carl.

14:25.295 --> 14:27.627
Oh, Lenny and Carl suck!

14:27.731 --> 14:31.326
Please don't tell Lenny and Carl I said that,
'cause if I ever lost 'em as friends-

14:31.434 --> 14:34.892
If Barney's that important to you,
you've gotta work it out.

14:35.004 --> 14:40.135
Old friends stick together, like O.J. and A.C.,
or the Falcon and the Snowman.

14:40.243 --> 14:42.177
Oh, why can't I have a nickname?

14:44.414 --> 14:46.143
<i>[ Groans ]</i>

14:46.249 --> 14:48.945
<i>- [ Whining, Panting ]
- [ Lisa ] Okay, that's it.</i>

14:50.053 --> 14:52.851
Looks good.
Oh, Bart...

14:52.956 --> 14:54.981
the bulldog didn't ante.

14:56.292 --> 14:58.760
Okay, on three. One, two-

14:58.862 --> 15:02.263
Perfect. Phone book cover,
here I come. Ha-ha!

15:02.365 --> 15:04.458
Hey! No fair!

15:04.567 --> 15:06.933
Oh, we'll never get a good picture.

15:07.036 --> 15:09.197
Hey, why don't we dump
spaghetti on Maggie's head?

15:09.305 --> 15:11.865
- That picture's a cliché.
- Picture?

15:15.645 --> 15:19.513
Hey, Apu, you got any of those potato chips
that give you diarrhea?

15:19.616 --> 15:21.982
I need to do a little
spring cleaning.

15:22.085 --> 15:24.610
They're in the safety cabinet.
I'll get the key.

15:24.721 --> 15:27.155
<i>[ Bell Dings ]</i>

15:27.257 --> 15:30.385
- Oh, hello, Homer.
- Barney.

15:30.493 --> 15:32.484
- Beer, huh?
- That's right.

15:32.595 --> 15:34.495
- Enjoy.
- That I will.

15:34.597 --> 15:36.497
- Then we agree.
- You keep thinking that.

15:36.599 --> 15:37.623
- I will.
- Me too.

15:37.734 --> 15:39.634
<i>- Good day then.
- Good day then is right.</i>

15:39.736 --> 15:41.067
- Ta.
- Ta-ta.

15:41.171 --> 15:44.038
<i>- [ Bell Dings ]
- Hey, you did not pay for that beer!</i>

15:44.140 --> 15:45.767
[ Yelps ]

15:45.875 --> 15:49.402
<i>[ Birds Twittering ]</i>

15:49.512 --> 15:52.743
Boy, you can see everything
from Mount Springfield-

15:52.849 --> 15:55.977
<i>- The Squidport, the old monorail-
- [ Bart ] The Rlay-Doh factory.</i>

15:59.222 --> 16:01.588
<i>- [ Buzzer Buzzes ]
- Crescent moon! Crescent moon!</i>

16:04.394 --> 16:06.760
Come on, Springfield.
Sparkle for me, baby.

16:06.863 --> 16:10.128
That's it. Heads up!

16:10.233 --> 16:13.031
Ow! Bart, that's hot.

16:13.136 --> 16:15.104
I said heads up.

16:21.845 --> 16:27.545
Lenny, Carl, I know a lot of people bad-mouth you
and focus on how you suck, but not me.

16:27.650 --> 16:29.550
To me, you're true-blue.

16:29.652 --> 16:32.678
<i>- Aw, thanks, big guy.
- Now dance, rummy.</i>

16:32.789 --> 16:37.317
- Okay. ## [ Humming Off-key ]
- Hiya, Moe.

16:37.427 --> 16:41.796
Well, if it isn't little Miss
''I'm not wasting my life anymore''...

16:41.898 --> 16:43.798
which he is.

16:43.900 --> 16:48.860
Moe, I've come here to make amends for
my disgraceful behavior over the last 20 years.

16:48.972 --> 16:51.440
- Oh, that's okay, Barn.
- No, it's not okay.

16:51.541 --> 16:54.442
I broke barstools,
befouled your broom closet...

16:54.544 --> 16:58.480
and made sweet love to your pool table,
which I then befouled.

16:58.581 --> 17:01.482
Well, that would explain
the drop-off in play.

17:01.584 --> 17:03.677
This is a Channel 6 News bulletin.

17:03.786 --> 17:06.414
Fire has broken out
on Mount Springfield...

17:06.521 --> 17:08.887
trapping two youngsters
and their camera.

17:08.992 --> 17:11.017
Oh, no. That's Bart and Lisa!

17:11.127 --> 17:14.358
Unfortunately, fire trucks are unavailable
to fight the blaze...

17:14.464 --> 17:18.332
<i>as they're all being used to film the new
Burt Reynolds movie, Fireball and Mudflap.</i>

17:18.434 --> 17:20.334
I caught up with Burt on the set.

17:20.435 --> 17:23.963
<i>So, Burt, tell us a little about
Fireball and Mudflap.</i>

17:24.073 --> 17:26.007
Well, I playJerry ''Fireball'' Mudflap...

17:26.108 --> 17:29.567
a feisty Supreme Court justice,
who's searching for his birth mother...

17:29.679 --> 17:32.079
while competing in
a cross-country fire truck race.

17:32.181 --> 17:34.581
It's garbage.

17:36.486 --> 17:39.080
Barney, you gotta fly us
up there and save my kids.

17:39.188 --> 17:41.656
I can't.
I've never flown solo.

17:41.758 --> 17:45.421
Barney, the call is from heroism.

17:45.528 --> 17:47.621
Will you accept the charges?

17:47.730 --> 17:50.528
<i>[ Groaning ]</i>

17:55.138 --> 17:57.106
Where are you going?
The fire's that way.

17:57.206 --> 18:00.505
I know. I know. I haven't
learned right turns yet.

18:00.610 --> 18:01.838
- Aaah! Look out!
- [ Shouts ]

18:01.945 --> 18:05.813
<i>- [ Shouts ]
- Aaah!</i>

18:06.849 --> 18:08.749
<i>- [ Grunts ]
- [ Horns Honking ]</i>

18:08.851 --> 18:10.546
[ Tires Screeching ]

18:10.653 --> 18:13.554
I can't do this.
My nerves are shot.

18:13.656 --> 18:16.284
<i>- [ Grunting ]
- [ Horn Honking ]</i>

18:16.392 --> 18:18.519
[ Tires Squealing ]

18:20.863 --> 18:24.355
- Beer! That's what I need!
- Barney, no! Don't!

18:24.467 --> 18:27.095
<i>Yes! I need it.
[ Groans ]</i>

18:27.203 --> 18:30.604
<i>No! You've gotta be sober for this.
Give me that.</i>

18:30.707 --> 18:33.198
<i>[ Gulping ]
Ew, it's warm.</i>

18:34.510 --> 18:37.001
- You can't drink 'em all.
- Oh, yes, I can.

18:37.113 --> 18:39.809
<i>- I'll-
- [ Grunting ] Give me that.</i>

18:45.521 --> 18:48.615
I won't let you give up now
when you worked so hard-

18:48.725 --> 18:52.388
[ Slurring ]
to be the greatest pal in the world.

18:52.495 --> 18:54.690
I love you.

18:54.797 --> 18:57.391
Let's not lose touch
after graduation.

18:57.500 --> 19:00.025
[ Snoring ]

19:01.070 --> 19:03.038
You brave man.

19:03.139 --> 19:05.334
You took six silver bullets for me.

19:05.441 --> 19:09.070
Stay away from my wife.
[ Mumbles ]

19:10.580 --> 19:12.707
Looks like it's up to me.

19:22.959 --> 19:25.223
- [ Sighs ]
- We should be safe up here.

19:25.328 --> 19:27.228
I'm pretty sure fires
can't climb trees.

19:27.330 --> 19:29.230
- Ow!
- Dad!

19:29.332 --> 19:33.428
- Hi, kids! [ Laughs ]
- Hang on. I'll throw you a ladder.

19:36.039 --> 19:38.030
[ Shouting ]

19:38.141 --> 19:41.406
<i>- [ Grunting ]
- [ Screams ] Get off!. Get off!.</i>

19:43.513 --> 19:45.481
<i>[ Groans ]</i>

19:45.581 --> 19:47.674
<i>[ Grunting ]</i>

19:49.152 --> 19:51.052
- Dad, help!
- Help!

19:51.154 --> 19:53.054
All right, I'm comin'.

19:53.156 --> 19:55.522
[ Both Shouting ]

19:55.625 --> 19:59.152
Let me know if you're gonna
do that again, Homer.

20:06.803 --> 20:08.771
[ Shouting ]

20:12.475 --> 20:16.434
- You did it, Dad!
- You can't prove I did it.

20:16.546 --> 20:19.344
No! You saved our lives.

20:19.449 --> 20:22.577
I could do a lot of things
if I had some money.

20:22.685 --> 20:25.176
<i>- What?
- Now there's a picture.</i>

20:26.355 --> 20:28.323
<i>[ Shutter Clicks ]</i>

20:31.994 --> 20:34.690
Kids! The new phone books are here...

20:34.797 --> 20:37.698
and your picture's on the cover!

20:37.800 --> 20:39.825
- All right!
- Whoa! Cool! Let me see!

20:39.936 --> 20:42.336
[ Screaming ]

20:42.438 --> 20:46.704
Isn't it adorable? I guess some
baby pictures were on that old roll of film.

20:46.809 --> 20:49.676
Oh, we'll be the laughingstock
of the whole town.

20:49.779 --> 20:52.009
Well, at least we won the bike.

20:52.115 --> 20:57.052
Actually, I took the picture,
so I gave my prize to the orphanage.

20:57.153 --> 20:58.347
- What?
- How could you?

20:58.454 --> 21:02.322
Just kidding.
I would never do that.

21:02.425 --> 21:04.518
<i>[ Gasping ]</i>

21:07.263 --> 21:11.165
- Well, I'm glad we're friends again.
- Yeah.

21:11.267 --> 21:15.135
- So what do you call this stuff?
- A double tall mocha latte.

21:16.272 --> 21:18.172
It's not bad.

21:18.274 --> 21:20.902
<i>Well, it ain't beer.</i>

21:21.010 --> 21:23.638
But at least I got
that monkey off my back.

21:23.746 --> 21:25.646
<i>[ Gulping ]
Ah.</i>

21:25.748 --> 21:27.648
<i>[ Gulping ]
Oh.</i>

21:27.750 --> 21:30.412
<i>[ Gulping ] Oh.
[ Burps ]</i>

21:30.520 --> 21:33.887
<i>Ha, ha. Nobody gets away from Moe.</i>

21:33.990 --> 21:35.787
Nobody.

21:35.892 --> 21:38.861
[ Steam Hissing ]

21:40.396 --> 21:42.591
<i>[ Laughing ]</i>

21:42.698 --> 21:44.598
<i>[ Coughing ]
Oh.</i>

21:44.700 --> 21:46.600
<i>[ Laughs, Coughs ]
Oh.</i>

22:25.708 --> 22:27.676
- [ Murmuring ]
- Shh!

